The paper discusses a mathematical model (Polya urn process) that finds applications in various problems, including competitions. The focus is on studying two statistics of competitions (duration and intensity) under different regimes for fitness and nonlinearity. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper deals with mathematical modeling and analysis, cs.MA and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories.
